        "title": "Warn when host approvals clamp exec security at startup",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Warn once during gateway startup when requested global `tools.exec` security is stricter-clamped by the local host approvals file.\n- Reuse the same clamp predicate as `openclaw exec-policy show`, keep the diagnostic read-only, and suppress node/sandbox-managed scopes.\n- Update troubleshooting guidance to point users at `openclaw exec-policy show` and the `yolo` preset instead of config-only edits.\n\nFixes #92206.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Gateway-local exec requests can be configured as `tools.exec.security=full` while host approvals still clamp the effective policy to `allowlist`; startup now surfaces that mismatch instead of silently leaving users to discover it later.\n\nReal environment tested: Local macOS source checkout, Node 24.16.0, isolated temp `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH` and `OPENCLAW_HOME`, no live channel/provider credentials. The gateway proof ran the patched source entry directly because the checkout launcher imports built `dist/entry.js`, which predates this source patch until a package build is made.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Created a temp config with `gateway.port=19878`, `tools.exec.host=gateway`, and `tools.exec.security=full`; created temp host approvals with `defaults.security=allowlist`; ran patched source gateway startup; captured the warning; sent SIGTERM immediately after the warning; and compared SHA-256 hashes for both temp files before/after.\n\nEvidence after fix: The patched gateway startup printed the warning before continuing startup, and both config and approvals hashes were unchanged:\n\n```text\ncommand=/Users/harjothk/.nvm/versions/node/v24.16.0/bin/node --import tsx src/entry.ts gateway run --allow-unconfigured --port 19878\nresult={\"code\":null,\"signal\":\"SIGTERM\"}\nconfigHashBefore=732dc1ea40142deaba0095980d863957581608b2a31581aee4bee22e1aa8a114\nconfigHashAfter=732dc1ea40142deaba0095980d863957581608b2a31581aee4bee22e1aa8a114\napprovalsHashBefore=7b667e80d008eef61df2c2f2615f397d81d7e0c8e23a3b5b1ffa1accef79df44\napprovalsHashAfter=7b667e80d008eef61df2c2f2615f397d81d7e0c8e23a3b5b1ffa1accef79df44\n--- captured patched gateway output (selected) ---\n2026-06-11T19:40:24.640-07:00 [gateway] loading configuration…\n2026-06-11T19:40:24.710-07:00 [gateway] tools.exec.security=full is clamped to allowlist by host approvals (/var/folders/lp/9mmnwgx50yn6n6j8yt6_p3400000gn/T/openclaw-92206-source-gateway-proof.4Sjbiu/home/.openclaw/exec-approvals.json defaults.security). Run \"openclaw exec-policy set --security full\" to synchronize host approvals, or \"openclaw exec-policy show\" for details.\n--- end captured patched gateway output ---\nwarningFound=true\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The patched gateway startup prints the warning once before normal startup proceeds; the effective security floor remains clamped to `allowlist`; neither config nor approvals are mutated.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live message-channel delivery and remote node runtime approvals; node and sandbox scopes are intentionally skipped by this startup warning and covered by focused unit tests.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- `PATH=/Users/harjothk/.nvm/versions/node/v24.16.0/bin:$PATH pnpm docs:list`\n- `/Users/harjothk/.nvm/versions/node/v24.16.0/bin/node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/gateway-cli/exec-policy-startup-warning.test.ts src/cli/gateway-cli/run.option-collisions.test.ts src/infra/exec-approvals-policy.test.ts src/cli/exec-policy-cli.test.ts src/commands/doctor-security.test.ts src/agents/exec-defaults.test.ts src/agents/bash-tools.exec.security-floor.test.ts`\n- `PATH=/Users/harjothk/.nvm/versions/node/v24.16.0/bin:$PATH pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `PATH=/Users/harjothk/.nvm/versions/node/v24.16.0/bin:$PATH node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/infra/exec-approvals-effective.ts src/cli/gateway-cli/exec-policy-startup-warning.ts src/cli/gateway-cli/exec-policy-startup-warning.test.ts src/cli/gateway-cli/run.ts src/cli/gateway-cli/run.option-collisions.test.ts`\n- External autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings, overall patch correct.\n\n## Notes\n\n- This PR is AI-assisted by Codex and was opened for maintainer/human review.\n- A candidate local agent transcript was found but not included because transcript insertion requires explicit approval and preview/review.\n",
